text: Laurence Dumont (born 2 June 1958) is a French politician and member of the French Socialist Party. In June 2017 she was elected to serve as Deputy for the 2nd constituency of Calvados in the French National Assembly. ==See also== * French legislative elections 2017 ==References== Category:1958 births Category:21st-century French women politicians Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 15th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Living people Category:People from Vincennes Category:Politicians from Normandy Category:Socialist Party (France) politicians Category:Women members of the National Assembly (France)
